    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-cou1-decision-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed the required level for Model Risk Level 2. Six factors are appropriately scoped out at MRL 2. The model is assessed as sufficiently credible for the intended COU: identification of worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device with RH < 1 acceptance criterion. The November 2025 turbulence-closure coefficient revision was reviewed by the lead analyst and judged not material to the geometric boundary conditions captured in the PIV dataset (vintage 2025-10-10) or the hemolysis bench dataset (vintage 2025-09-22); accordingly, no new experimental campaign was commissioned prior to submission. This determination is documented in internal memo MFM-2025-114 and accepted by the credibility assessment team.",
